         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 3 September 1875. ¶  ¶ I owe you my best thanks, dear Mr Blytt, for your kindness in having sent me your fine publications, ¶  for which I gratefully offer a reciprocal gift. You do not s...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">75.09.03a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Axel Blytt</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Brevs. nr. 66., Universitetsbiblioteket, Oslo.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">am 3 Sept. 1875.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich schuldige</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">schulde</seg>
                     <seg style="">?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <seg style=""> Ihnen meinen besten Dank, sehr geehrter Herr Blytt, für Ihre Güte mir Ihre schönen Schriften gesandt zu haben, für welche ich dankbar eine Gegengabe mache. Sie scheinen <name key="Chenolea%20hirsuta">Chenolea hirsuta</name> (<name key="Kochia%20hirsuta">Kochia hirsuta</name> Nolte) nicht gefunden zu haben, welche sicher bei Ihnen vorkommt, aber leicht in der kahlen Form mit <name key="Suaeda%20maritima">Suaeda maritima</name> verwechselt werden kann, worüber ich weitläufig in Trimen's Journal vor 3 Jahren berichtet habe. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Können Sie mir gütig sagen, ob unser Freund Ascherson oder ich selbst Priorität haben in der Vereinigung von Blitum mit Chenopodium. Ich nannte vor mehreren Jahren das <name key="Blitum%20virgatum">Blitum virgatum</name> in Caruel's giornale Chenopodium Blitum, unter welchem Namen es auch in meiner Abhandlung über Nutz-Pflanzen in dem Band unserer Acclimation-Society für 1873 vorkommt.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mit freundlichster Ergebenheit Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Ich besitze Ascherson's Flora von Brandenburg nicht, weiss auch nicht wann solche erschien.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">3 September 1875.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I owe you my best thanks, dear Mr Blytt, for your kindness in having sent me your fine publications,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Although there are no inscriptions, it is probable that Blytt sent the copies of Blytt (1869) and <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Blytt (1870) that are still in the Library at MEL, which also holds the second (1874) and third (1876) volumes of M. Blytt &amp; A. Blytt (1861-76); the library lacks the first volume (1861).</p>
               </note> for which I gratefully offer a reciprocal gift. You do not seem to have found <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Chenolea%20hirsuta">Chenolea hirsuta</name>
               </seg> (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Kochia%20hirsuta">Kochia hirsuta</name>
               </seg> Nolte), which should surely occur in your area, but in its bare form can easily be mistaken for <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Suaeda%20maritima">Suaeda maritima</name>
               </seg>; I have written at length about this in Trimen's journal 3 years ago.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See B73.06.01.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would you be so kind as to tell me if our friend Ascherson or I has priority in uniting <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Blitum</seg> with <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Chenopodium</seg>?<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Ascherson's reduction was in Ascheron (1864), p. 572.</p>
               </note> Several years ago I changed <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Blitum%20virgatum">Blitum virgatum</name>
               </seg> to <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Chenopodium%20blitum">Chenopodium blitum</name>
               </seg> in Caruel's journal,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Under the heading 'Lavori del Dr Mueller sulle Chenopodiacee', <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Nuovo giornale botanico italiano</seg>, vol. 2 (1870), p. 314, there is a note of an undated letter, M to T. Caruel, 1870 (in this edition as 70-06-00b), in which the change is reported, but without giving a detailed rationale.</p>
               </note> and it is also found under this name in my publication on useful plants in the volume for 1873 of our Acclimatisation Society.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See B74.13.06, p. 60.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With my kindest respects your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I do not own Ascherson's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Flora von Brandenburg</seg>,<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Ascherson (1864). There is an incomplete copy at MEL, but it is not known when it was added to the Library.</p>
               </note> nor do I know when it was published.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Blitum%20virgatum">Blitum virgatum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Chenolea%20hirsuta">Chenolea hirsuta</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Chenopodium%20blitum">Chenopodium blitum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Kochia%20hirsuta">Kochia hirsuta</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Suaeda%20maritima">Suaeda maritima</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
